Anonymous Sat 20 Jul 2024 19:13:14 No.67556637 Report
Quoted By: >>67556786 >>67556834
>>67556296
>Finally got my first hmofa novel edited
You might want to get someone native English to edit for you, which is what I thought you meant by the above.

>I finally got my first /hmofa/ novel edited
This means you hired someone to do it after a long delay. This is because "got" indicates receipt of the edited text.
>I've finally gotten my first /hmofa/ novel edited.
This means that you took a long time to do it, but have completed the editing yourself. Perfect past indicates a process has completed, which would imply something that took you a while to do.

In spoken English, there's also an inflection difference. You would not stress the tone of "edited" if it was hired out, but stress "edited" if you've done it yourself.

(The more you know!)

>Any feedback is appreciated.
Second person is garbage. Obviously that's a result of
>started as a greentext
but unless you're doing stream of consciousness or an intentionally disorienting scene, there's almost no place for second person in actual writing.

Not this doomposting shit again. NTA, but I agree about second person. It's fine for greentexts, but greentexts are short short fiction. Usually a few hundred words.
